Package com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface Summary
IBaseline A Baseline represents an immutable Configuration of a set of Versionables (i.e. it records the StateId of a subset of the Versionables in a Repository), and the history of ChangeSets which led up to the Configuration.
IBaselineHandle Represents a handle to a baseline item.
IBaselineSet A BaselineSet represents an immutable collection of baselines.
IBaselineSetHandle Represents a handle to a baseline set item.
IChange Represents a change (add, delete, modify) to a single versionable item.
IChangeHistoryEntry Represents an entry in a change history.
IChangeHistoryEntryChange Represents an entry in a change history that is a change set.
IChangeSet Represents a change set.
IChangeSetHandle Represents a handle to a change set item.
IComponent Represents a component known to the repository.
IComponentHandle Represents a handle to a component item.
IComponentInfo Represents the audit trail for a component in a workspace.
IContextHandle Mixin interface to identify items which can have configurations and change histories.
ICurrentComponentInfo Represents the audit trail for a component currently in a workspace.
IFlowEntry An entry in a flow table.
IFlowNode Marker interface which indicates that an interface can serve as a target or source for the flowing of changes throughout the system.
IFlowNodeHandle Represents the handle to a FlowNode auditable.
IFlowTable Represent a table of flow entries describing nominal flows between the owning workspace and any number of targets.
IFolder Represents a folder in the repository.
IFolderHandle Represents a handle to a folder item ((@link IFolder}).
IItemInfoException Exception interface which describes a generic type of exception that returns an IItemInfoData].
ILinksConfiguration Linking related configuration data for SCM operations.
IPastComponentInfo Represents the meta information about the audit trail for a component no longer in a workspace.
IRepositoryProgressMonitor A repository progress monitor is a persistent item which allows support for cancellation in RPC style service methods.
IRepositoryProgressMonitorHandle Represents a handle to a repository progress monitor.
IScmEvents Constants and helpers for change events generated by the server for interesting SCM operations.
IScmProcessConfiguration Process related configuration data for SCM operations.
IScmProperties  
IScmWorkspaceProperties  
IVersionable Represents an SCM versionable container type (e.g. file, folder, or symbolic link).
IVersionableHandle Represents a handle to a SCM versionable item ((@link IVersionable}).
IVersionedContent Represents a description of content that is stored in the repository.
IWorkspace Represents a workspace qua auditable item.
IWorkspaceHandle Represents a handle to a workspace qua auditable item.
UpdatesTeamAdvisorView Indicates that a method call should cause the TeamAdvisorView to refresh.
 

Class Summary
AcceptFlags This class identifies different flags for the resuming change sets into a workspace.
ContentHash Wrapper for the hash of versionable content
FlowFlags  
IRepositoryProgressMonitor.RepositoryMonitorFactory A helper factory for creating repository monitors.
ScmCommon  
WorkspaceComparisonFlags Flags used to describe different variations of workspace comparison.
 

Exception Summary
AcceptSuspendedChangeSetException Exception indicating that a change set could not be resumed as it was not considered to be suspended by the contributor.
ActiveChangeSetsException Server-side exception indicating that a repository operation failed because the workspace has open active change sets.
ActiveChangeSetsOverlapException Exception indicating that active suspended change sets could not be resumed as they overlapped with an active change set in the workspace.
ChangeSetAlreadyInHistoryException Exception indicating that a change set could not be accepted as it already existed in the recent era of the target change history.
ChangeSetsNotOutgoingException Exception indicating that change sets could not be delivered as they were not considered outgoing in the comparison between the source and target workspace or stream.
CompareWorkspacesException  
CompletedChangeSetException Exception which indicates that an operation failed because the change set is in a completed state instead of active.
ComponentNotInWorkspaceException Exception indicating that an operation was requested on a workspace for a component which is not in that workspace.
ConflictsProhibitOperationException Exception which indicates that the operation could not be completed as the workspace/component in question contains conflicts.
ContentHashAlgorithmException An exception that indicates a problem with the hashing algorithm used for versioned content.
CrossComponentMoveOverlapsActiveException This exception indicates that the cross-component move operation failed because there are active changes in the workspace which overlap with the changes that need to be created to perform the cross-component move.
DeleteSubtreeOverlapsException Exception indicating that change sets could not be delivered since they would create conflicts in the target stream or workspace.
DeliveryIntroducesConflictsException Exception indicating that change sets could not be delivered since they would create conflicts in the target stream or workspace.
DiscardInitialBaselineException Exception which indicates that discarding a change set fails because it is in the initial baseline
DiscardNotInHistoryException Exception which indicates that discarding a change set fails because it is not in the change history
FolderEntryConflictException Exception that indicates that a commit operation has failed due to conflicting names in the states saved or selected with respect to other versionables who share the same parent.
FolderParentageCycleException Exception that indicates that a commit operation has failed, as the states saved or selected would introduce a cycle in the configuration with respect to folder parentage.
GapException Exception indicating that change sets could not be accepted since they would create gaps in the change history.
IllegalRootFolderModificationException Exception which indicates that a commit operation has failed as it would create an invalid state for the root folder of a component's configuration.
IllegalSuspendException Exception that indicates a suspend operation is going to fail because the scm service is being asked to suspend an active change set without a context to the workspace for which it is active within.
InvalidAuthenticationTokenException Exception indicating the remote repository rejected the authentication information supplied by the user to the repository being called.
InvalidStreamOperationException Exception which indicates that a particular SCM operation is valid only for workspaces and not streams.
InvalidWorkspaceOperationException Exception which indicates that a particular SCM operation is valid only for streams and not workspaces.
ItemAlreadyInActiveChangeSetException This class is an exception which indicates that a commit operation has failed since the item is already referenced in a different active change set than the one indicated in the call to commit.
ItemLockedInStreamException  
LockOperationFailureException Exception indicating that a versionable locking operation failed.
LockTimeoutException Exception indicating that change sets could not be accepted since they would create gaps in the change history.
NWayConflictUnsupportedException Exception which indicates that the scm operation has failed, as it would produce a change history where there would be an n-way conflict, for n > 2, which is currently unsupported.
OutstandingConflictsException Exception indicating that change sets could not be delivered as the source workspace has outstanding conflicts which need to be resolved.
ProducesOrphansInConfigurationException Exception which indicates that the current operation has failed because it would have produced an invalid configuration in the workspace which it attempted to modify.
ResumeNonSuspendedChangeSetException Exception indicating that a change set could not be resumed as it was not considered to be suspended by the contributor.
SyncReportInappropriateException Exception indicating that a change history sync report is not appropriate for the operation it is sent in for.
VersionedContentNotFound
